5:
There are no signs of the dragon
here.
9:
We aren't the only adventurers on
this expedition. If we keep pressing,
we're bound to find it eventually.
11:
Let's forge ahead as we have been.
Stay alert!
17:
Incoming report from the
Dracohazard Scouts! They've
encountered a dragon—and a
particularly strong one, at that.
21:
No doubt that's the one causing all
the trouble lately.
25:
I don't know about that. The thing is,
this particular dragon seems to
have been around for more than 10
years.
29:
From that long ago? What has it
been doing that entire time?
33:
Well, up until now, the nearby village
had been offering up sacrifices to
the dragon.
40:
So they picked someone out to die
and went on livin' their lives,
business as usual?
43:
And now suddenly they're the
victims, come beggin' for help?
What a load of crap.
47:
They were likely incapable of
helping themselves. Perhaps they
had no other recourse but to offer
up sacrifices...
52:
But we can put an end to this
tragedy. All we need to do is slay the
dragon—
61: Damn, this one is the real deal, huh.
69:
It couldn't be... Why is it in a place
like this?
And why is it taking sacrifices?!
73:
Compose yourself, great dragon!
We wish to know why one as great
as yourself is asking for sacrifices!
81:
That's right. I am the champion,
Light.
85:
I see.
Is this the Law of Ancients you spoke
of, Rams?
89: But I will not fall this day—I cannot.
93: We have no choice but to fight...
99:
You've got it wrong, Lord Schult isn't
like that! Please!
Everyone, if you would just listen to
me...
105: What do you have to say?
109:
I never asked for this. I never made
demands for any sacrifice.
116:
I was... chasing the thunder,
traversing the skies... Before I
realized it, I found myself in this
world.
117:
Then the humans came. At first, they
bore their steel against me.
119:
As time passed, their assault waned,
and they came to me bearing
something else...
125:
Sacrifices. Though I did not ask, they
offered them. Each time a storm
raged, a new sacrifice was brought
to me.
128:
My name is Lucia, and I was offered
up in this precise manner... Lord
Schult has been a great help to
me—and to all of us who were
sacrificed.
131:
So Schult didn't actually do anything
wrong?
133:
Then why not just return to your
village and explain the whole
situation?
136: If they go... they will die.
139:
I did return to the village once. But
the villagers exiled me—they said I
had forsaken my role as sacrifice.
142:
People can be real despicable
sometimes...
146:
I've understood the circumstances.
But the entire Adventurer's Guild has
already mobilized—I'm not sure if we
can prevent a conflict.
149: I cannot be bested by humans.
158: Come with us to Starview Village.
161:
No one will pursue you there.
You will be safe.
166:
I cannot—I must watch over Lucia
and the others. They rely on me.
169:
Lord Schult, please do not worry
about us! We will be fine on our
own...
173:
Why don't you come with us too,
Lucia? You can bring the others as
well.
175:
In the meantime, we can make up
some sort of story about how we
defeated the dragon, or how it ran
away or something.
184:
Hahaha!
You humans are... very different
from what I expected.
186:
Fascinating.
I had forgotten what it feels like to
be impressed.
189:
I don't think I've ever heard Lord
Schult laugh like this before!
192:
I understand now, humans.
I will go with you.
194:
Champion Light, you and your
comrades have my thanks.
198:
Of course.
Welcome to Starview Village.
203:
What business do you have with me,
Champion?
207:
The name Schult... I've read it before,
in the ancient texts. I believe you
were referred to as the Gale of
Calamity.
208:
The text described you as a being
that indiscriminately cut down all
that stood in your path—a whirlwind
of cataclysmic proportions.
211:
I can't help but wonder, great
dragon... Why would someone like
that choose to help those sacrificed
girls?
215:
Do not think me the same as King
Vagner. My days of pretending to be
a storm are long behind me.
216:
Yes, for what felt like eternity I stood
idle, no longer wishing for anything. I
did nothing but wait for my destiny.
For the Law of Ancients.
219:
But one day, when I looked into
Lucia's eyes, everything changed. A
desire within me waxed. A desire to
do something different.
224:
You don't know? It's hard to imagine
those words coming out of a
dragon's mouth.
227:
I am different from other dragons. It
has been... a long time since I
thought of these matters and
conversed on them.
231:
I see. My apologies. It is clear to me
now that your intentions are noble...
You are not to be feared.
235:
I am grateful to have an ally as
strong as you on our side.
May our bonds grow ever stronger,
great dragon.
239:
I see in his eyes... that same thing I
saw in Lucia's.
241:
The will to fight on, even in the face
of fear, even after endless setbacks.
How very... human.
